      "Injured person flown to onshore medical facility",
      "Surgery performed on 27 September 2021 to repair thumb damage"
    ],
    "summary": "On 25 September 2021 at approximately 1030 hours, a contract operator for Crosby Energy Services tripped on uneven deck grating while assisting a construction crew in moving a sheet of tin metal. In attempting to stop the fall, the injured person grabbed the sharp edge of the tin metal, which cut through inadequate work gloves and caused a laceration to the left thumb. The injured person was transported to a hospital in Houma, LA for treatment beyond first aid and underwent surgery on 27 September 2021.",
